<subSubSection pageNumber="868" type="discussion">
<paragraph pageNumber="868">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="868">Note: 
<taxonomicName authority="Linnaeus (1760)" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1760" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rutaceae" genus="Spathalea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Sapindales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
Spathalea 
<bibRefCitation pageNumber="868" refId="references.r243">Linnaeus (1760)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
was published without a description and is therefore not validly published under Art. 42.1. The name was validated in 1762, as 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rutaceae" genus="Spathelia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Sapindales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="868">Spathelia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and is a conserved name. Although some authors (e.g. Fawcett &amp; Rendle, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="868">Fl. Jamaica</emphasis>
4: 193. 1920) have taken up 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1760" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rutaceae" genus="Spathalea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Sapindales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="sorbifolia">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="868">Spathalea sorbifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, this is incorrect.
</paragraph>
